 the Rights of the Child. This is the only book to focus specifically on the application of evidence to service delivery within youth justice. It will be an essential text for social work students undertaking university-based modules or practice-based learning in services which address youth crime and youth justice, as well as other students interested in the application of criminology and youth justice principles. It will also be valuable for practitioners involved in delivering youth justice services, including those on post-qualifying social work training courses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aJuvenile justice, Administration ofzGreat Britain. 0aJuvenile justice, Administration of. 0aSocial work with juvenile delinquentszGreat Britain. 0aSocial work with juvenile delinquents. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978186134839540uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447342663?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447342663423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447342663/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013